    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002698_0001" n="0001"/> 
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="center"><placeName>R. Zambesi</placeName> <date when="1862-03-04">4<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="words"/>1862</date></dateline>
<lb/>
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sir</salute></opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/>many thanks
<lb/>for your kind attentions
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> L</persName> &amp; self in sending
<lb/>the letters &amp; Newspapers
<lb/>which came all safely
<lb/>to hand - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>The <term type="animal">mules</term> too
<lb/>were in excellent condition
<lb/>and seem fine strong
<lb/>animals - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>The carts &amp;
<lb/>harness all right - By the
<lb/>kind assistance of
<lb/><persName><term type="occupationn">Captain</term> Wilson</persName> &amp; his officers
<lb/>we had the greater part
<lb/>of the hull put aboard
<lb/>the Pioneer but the
<lb/><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName> is in high
<lb/>flood and more rapid
<lb/>than we ever saw it

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>It is indeed far too strong
<lb/>a current for the Pioneer
<lb/>with <measure>35 tons</measure> in her, so
<lb/>after spending 3 weeks in
<lb/>getting up to <settlement type="village">Shupanga</settlement>
<lb/>we are obliged to unload -
<lb/>put the hull together &amp;
<lb/>tow her <hi rend="below">^</hi><hi rend="above">the new one</hi> up to the
<lb/>cataracts - This will detain
<lb/>us till <date when="1862-05"><choice><sic>may</sic><corr>May</corr></choice></date> - </p>
<lb/><p>Seeing that we made
<lb/>such miserably slow
<lb/>progress <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Wilson</persName>
<lb/>acceded to the request of
<lb/><persName>Miss Mackenzie</persName> to be
<lb/>taken forward to the
<lb/><term type="occupation">bishop</term> in his gig - The
<lb/><term type="occupation">bishop</term> was not found
<lb/>at the <placeName>Ruo</placeName> as he engaged<!-- part of this extends to the other page- do we mark that? SF -->

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>to be and we hear by the
<lb/>return of one boat from
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName> the <term type="occupation">Captain</term> had gone
<lb/>on to near the cataracts
<lb/>where he would send up
<lb/>for the <term type="occupation">bishop</term> and deliver
<lb/>up his charge - she
<lb/>is very weakly at best
<lb/>and was ill when they 
<lb/>were kept by the return
<lb/>boat. There is no doubt
<lb/>but Ladies would be
<lb/>a great boon to the
<lb/>mission if they were
<lb/>strong as <persName>Mrs.Burrup</persName>
<lb/>appears to be, but
<lb/><persName>Miss Mackenzie</persName>'s is
<lb/>a peculiar case &amp;
<lb/>I have my fears

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/>Believe me
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Dear Sir</p>

<lb/><closer rend="center"><salute>Most Truly yours</salute>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>
<lb/><trailer><del type="cancelled"><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></del> Esq.</trailer>

            </div>
